Count 1 - Possess Methamphetamine with Intent to Deliver - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 - 5.   Motion granted.    Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
4) Maintain full-time work/school combination; 
5) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Twelve (12) months jail; Ten (10) months up front, under the Huber Law, to commence on 06-23-16 by 6:00 p.m.   Two (2) months stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion.   Court will authorize transfer to Calumet or Outagamie County Jail as long as there is no electronic monitoring or in the alternative travel outside the county for purposes of employment.  
Minutes.
